Reasoning: The paper discusses the potential citation advantage of open access articles in a multidisciplinary context, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The sub-category cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely as it deals with the dissemination and access to scholarly publications. The sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also likely as they involve research on publication and citation analysis. The sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are less likely but still possible as they may involve research on the impact of open access on scholarly communication and dissemination.
